            {
                "numero": 4,
                "titre": "Step 4: Tests and Results",
                "solutions": [
                    {
                        "objectif": "",
                        "materiaux_outils": [],
                        "etapes": [
                            {
                                "titre": "To test how well this heater works I will do the experiment in a bathroom measuring 2.3 by 1.8m and 2.1m high, which is approximately 8.7 m³",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "So on the first day I will leave the thermometer in the bathroom from 1 to 4 pm to see the temperature evolution without a heater.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "As the bathroom has \"good\" thermal insulation, the temperature remained at 16.8 ºC from 1 to 4 pm",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "The next morning at 9 am the bathroom was at 17.4ºC because it had been heated the night before (but with the heater off, of course) and I left the candle heater there to see how the temperature would change.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "After an hour the temperature was 18.4ºc, it was 1ºc higher than without the candle heater, but it probably rose soon because the thermometer was 1m above the heater, I went to check it after another hour and it was still at the same temperature, I think that from then on it didn't get much warmer because the bathroom door was opened several times.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "In short, this heater is good for emergency situations and blackouts, or for small places that have good ventilation, but for large areas it won't make a big difference because its heating power is just a fraction of that of an electric heater.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "But if you are looking for an off grid heater I would probably recommend a paraffin heater, as it is safer and heats up more",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Besides, this heater is also good for decorating",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
